column5: After getting a lot of great information from fellow board members, I was able to land my first white fish through ice!  one natural fish, one fin clipped   stomach content   boneless and brown fat free   Bon appetite!
congrats! looks like some nice fish and good eatin, thanks for sharing!
Very nice and a great looking meal. Congrats to you!
Looks like A nice meal, Whitefish are a ugly fish but taste amazing.

They're both stocked fish  The one to the right has it's left pectoral clipped and the one to the left has it's adipose fin clipped.  I had my first taste of fried whitie a couple weeks ago and it's delicious.
Did you find that they smell like cucumbers? LOL
What, no flippin noodles! Your mom makes great noodles, they should be on every plate you have! Congrats on the catch and that plate looks delicious! HH
WTG young_one     Congrats
Yep, adipose clip.   So it's not just me....LOL  Congratuations Young One, they are yummy, no doubt about it.
Nicely done, young_one....no question they are extremely tasty!
Well done.Nice fried fish too.    Yep they sure do.
The naturals are a lot smaller on average then those fish and have a distinct gold tinge to them, gotta make sure you let those ones go
and hear I was under the impression they had a date with my smoker...
Brooklyn is not exactly down the street from my place I'll rain check the next available whitie
LOL, what do you mean?  It's only a full hour round trip out of your way... it's all good y_o

I disagree, 35 years I've fished that lake with whitefish a main target and I totally disagree with your statement Bill.  Colour variations and size have nothing to do with the stocked vs. natural population.
That's cool, I've spent quite a few days out there in the past 3 years.   I'm not the only one that's noticed this
Non the less,nice to see natural whities and lakers.
You just had to go and tease everyone didnt you .  Nice going, good looking fish and i have to agree with Headhunter, wheres those great noodles?
Noodles....  Armageddon!  G
AHHAHAHAHAHA  you pay now!
